<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="nl" lang="nl"><head><title>IE margin-right inherit bug</title>

<style>
body { font-size: 12px; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
div#cntContent {
	border: 1px solid green;
	margin-right: 150px;
}

fieldset {
	margin: 0;
	padding: 0;
	border: 1px solid red;
	width: 340px;

}

input, label { float: left; }
form br { clear: both; }
label { width: 200px; }
</style></head>

<body>
<h2>IE margin-right inherit bug</h2>
<p>When using a margin on a parent container with a child container
inside and in there form elements then the margin of the parent
container gets inherited to the form elements, and it can't be removed
by a margin 0.</p>

<p>The affected form elements are
input types, checkboxes, radiobuttons and textareas</p>

<p>The solution is to put an OVERFLOW: HIDDEN on the child container.</p>

All fieldsets are 340px<br>
Green parent has a margin right of 150px<br>
<div style="border-left: 1px solid blue; border-right: 1px solid blue; position: absolute; right: 0pt; width: 148px; text-align: center;"><span style="padding: 0pt 5px; position: relative; top: 10px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); z-index: 5;">width 150px</span><br>
</div>
<div style="border-top: 1px solid blue; position: absolute; right: 0pt; width: 148px; height: 1px; z-index: 1; margin-top: 8px;"></div>

	<div id="cntContent">
		<form>
			<div style="border-left: 1px solid blue; border-right: 1px solid blue; margin-left: 310px; width: 150px; text-align: center;"><span style="padding: 0pt 5px; position: relative; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); z-index: 5;">width 150px</span><br>
			</div>
			<div style="border-top: 1px solid blue; margin-left: 310px; position: relative; top: -8px; width: 150px; height: 1px; z-index: 1;"></div>
			<fieldset>
				<label for="versturen">fieldset</label>
				<input name="but1" value="but1" type="submit">
				<input name="but2" value="but2" type="submit">
				<input name="but3" value="but3" type="submit"><br>
			</fieldset><br>
			<fieldset style="overflow: hidden;">
				<label for="versturen">same fieldset with overflow hidden</label>
				<input name="but1" value="but1" type="submit">
				<input name="but2" value="but2" type="submit">
				<input name="but3" value="but3" type="submit"><br>
			</fieldset><br>
			<fieldset>
				<label for="versturen">fieldset</label>
				<input name="text1" value="text1" size="13" type="text"><br>
			</fieldset><br>
			<fieldset style="overflow: hidden;">
				<label for="versturen">same fieldset with overflow hidden</label>
				<input name="text1" value="text1" size="13" type="text"><br>
			</fieldset><br>
			<fieldset>
				<label for="versturen">fieldset</label>
				<select><option>Not affected</option><option>Aint it weird</option></select>
			</fieldset><br>
			<fieldset style="overflow: hidden;">
				<label for="versturen">same fieldset with overflow hidden</label>
				<select><option>Not affected</option><option>Aint it weird</option></select>
			</fieldset><br>
			<div style="border-left: 1px solid blue; border-right: 1px solid blue; margin-top: 4px; width: 340px; text-align: center;"><span style="padding: 0pt 5px; position: relative; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); z-index: 5;">width 340px</span><br>
			</div>
			<div style="border-top: 1px solid blue; position: relative; top: -8px; width: 340px; height: 1px; z-index: 1;"></div>
		</form>
	</div>
</body></html>